<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Skrimgeour Kuchenhyrst:
[B]Dartanian - 

I have been around, I read a lot, just don't post much (too many other boards have made me their admins/spokesperson).

Rayne - thanks. The epic helped a lot on our first Sev raid on Monday.

Rayne, I think the Lodizal comparison is comparing apples to oranges. (And yes, a few folks in the Haven have Lodizal items from killing him)

You stated:
He drops the shells necessary for the shield and also a map part for one of the best face pieces in the game. The "rule" on him is first engaged owns the spawn until one or the other is dead. People sit out there looking for him, but if they don't engage quickly (within seconds) are they entitled to the spawn? Of course not, he who engages first gets it. 

I reply:
Lodizal isn't triggered like Zordak is. There is room to kite Lodizal (and Faydedar) which is not an option for Ragefire (I think) and Lodizal is on a much shorter timer. Anyone can DO Lodizal, there is no level limit on him. Verant did but a level limit on epics.....

And yes, I do think it is different. There are reasons our server has rotations on big targets. We have collectively deciced they are different than Lodizal, the Overking, etc.

Does Karana have a rotation on Ragefire? Nope. And I am strongly opposed to any rotation. My belief is whatever cleric wants to park his purple butt down there and wait on the spawn and keep the FGs cleared until that stupid Ragefire appears should get it, and there shouldn't be up to a 20 hour delay while waiting for the guild scheduled to get it gets it (but that is just me). He spawns TOO frequently to be on a roation, but is in a class where some civilized discourse should occur.

Rayne, there is debate anytime you make rules, and can always be abuse (heh heh you know that from Karana) Just stating my feelings.

Oh, and EanneJohnson. I would like to suggest you read a few posts on this board. We try to be relatively civilized here and not call each others 'thieves'. Especially blanket statements about all clerics. 

And Trawma, I am living proof that you don't need to CRUSH others to get the epic. Heck, Karana is proof of that. Recently a very small guild on out server camped Ragefire for the entire 72 hours. Everytime I was on, they were in SolB waiting. You know what, eventally Rage popped and they probably didn't have the forces to take him. I volunteered to come help (I had never met the cleric before in my life) and brought along a few high level friends. A few friends from other guilds also showed up as well as a cleric from one of the more quick-to-mobilize guilds on the server. That cleric EASILY could have gotten his guild together to take it, but he helped as long as he could have the camp afterwards. There was no *crushing* involved. There was respect, some possible mashocism (I couldn't beleive I was going to help someone get their epic when I wanted it so much), and common decency.

Skrimgeour Kuchenhyrst
57th level Templar of Mithaniel Marr
The Haven
AoVB
Karana




[This message has been edited by Skrimgeour Kuchenhyrst (edited 05-09-2001).][/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
